void gtrack_matrixComputePJT ( float *  P,
float *  J,
float *  PJ 
)

Description
This function is used to multiply two matrices. First matrix P is of size 6x6, the second one is of the size 3x6. The second matrix is being transposed first. Matrices are all real, single precision floating point. Matrices are in row-major order

Parameters
[in]PMatrix P
[in]JMatrix J
[out]PJMatrix PJ = P(6,6) X J(3,6)T
Return values
None
